-- S&P 500 Extends Loss as Bernanke Says Fed’s Power `Not Infinite’
-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 2012-11-20T18:17:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-20/s-p-500-extends-loss-as-bernanke-says-fed-s-power-not-infinite-.html
U.S. stocks extended losses as
Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke said the central bank’s
ability to offset economic headwinds are “not infinite” and
business confidence has been “pretty low.”  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index lost 0.4 percent to
1,381.38 at 1:16 p.m. in  New York   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
